## Wushu

Wushu provides students with a holistic education that nurtures resilience, discipline, teamwork and sportsmanship. Students engage in structured lessons that build character, perseverance and a growth mindset, preparing them for life challenges.

Wushu not only strengthens their physical health but also shapes their character. During CCA, students learn to care for their weapons and maintain training equipment, thus instilling a sense of responsibility. Though training can be tiring, they build resilience and tenacity as they spur one another on. As they work together with their peers, they learn the value of teamwork and forge friendships for life.

Our Wushu students have the opportunities to perform in school events such as Chinese New Year Celebration, Speech Day and CCA Carnival. Selected students also participate in National School Games Wushu Championships and have consistently proven themselves on the National platform.
